3. Production Issue: Customers Receiving the Same Email Three Times
=================================================================================================================================================================
Problem Statement

In production, customers reported that they were receiving the same email three times instead of once.

Application Flow

Our application uses cron jobs configured in the gui.properties file. These schedulers automatically trigger different functionalities at predefined intervals. The email scheduler was configured to execute every 30 minutes.

Investigation

The scheduler was running on the .52 application server, which had three JVM instances. To identify the root cause, we added additional debug loggers in the code and deployed the changes to the UAT environment for testing.

During analysis, we observed that every time the email scheduler was triggered, it executed simultaneously on all three JVMs. Since each JVM independently picked up the same email records, the same email was processed and sent three times to customers.

Root Cause

The scheduler was active on all three JVMs of the same server, resulting in duplicate processing of the email jobs.

Solution

We implemented a flag-based scheduler execution mechanism.

At the code level, we introduced an isScheduler flag and enabled it only for JVM-1 on the .52 server. The flag was disabled for the remaining JVMs.

As a result, only JVM-1 executes the email scheduler every 30 minutes, while the other JVMs continue serving application requests without triggering the scheduler.

Result
Duplicate email issue was completely resolved.
Customers started receiving only one email per scheduled execution.
Scheduler execution became controlled and consistent across the clustered environment.
The fix was validated in UAT and successfully deployed to Production.

